The paper discusses a security technique for IoT networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of ARM TrustZone chips, which are commonly used in embedded systems (cs.SY) and distributed hash tables, which are commonly used in distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of a prototype, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
